35:26.250 --> 35:28.169
are naturally bad,

35:28.336 --> 35:31.172
so when something good happens,
it's only a matter of time

35:31.339 --> 35:33.466
before
that animal's true nature

35:33.633 --> 35:36.385
rears its ugly head.

35:37.011 --> 35:39.722
How much longer
can we afford to wait?

35:41.307 --> 35:43.935
You keep track of days,
numbering the years for scribes

35:44.101 --> 35:46.187
that record human history.

35:47.313 --> 35:48.856
Do you see progress?

35:50.483 --> 35:54.487
I count 1, 2, 3
African Gods in this room,

35:55.279 --> 35:57.573
and two of them want
to exercise restraint,

35:58.115 --> 36:00.243
and let the donkey-work continue

36:00.409 --> 36:03.579
while you live your best life!

36:04.705 --> 36:07.041
War is upon us!

36:07.708 --> 36:10.503
An old white
lady is dead.

36:11.879 --> 36:14.757
Wednesday avenges
Zorya Vechernyaya,

36:14.924 --> 36:17.051
but if it was
a dead black lady,

36:19.011 --> 36:20.888
like this sweet old soul,

36:22.807 --> 36:24.392
Czernobog's hammer...

36:27.103 --> 36:28.563
...would not swing.

36:33.276 --> 36:35.486
Your words move me, Anansi.

36:38.030 --> 36:39.490
You see me.

36:40.491 --> 36:42.493
You and Ibis see the Goddess,

36:43.953 --> 36:45.246
the Queen.

36:46.330 --> 36:48.875
These men today look
right through me.

37:06.517 --> 37:08.728
This country has done things
to us.

37:10.146 --> 37:14.150
We have done things to us.

37:16.193 --> 37:17.945
So, what do you propose?

37:19.155 --> 37:21.532
I propose we have a drink.

37:30.166 --> 37:32.543
A King needs a Queen.

37:34.128 --> 37:36.213
The death of Argus
left an opening.

37:36.923 --> 37:38.507
Argus was a relic,

37:38.674 --> 37:41.260
a desiccating, necrotising,

37:41.427 --> 37:44.639
geriatric, organic sack
of redundancies.

37:48.225 --> 37:50.519
CCTV?

37:50.686 --> 37:52.480
Fuck that noise!

37:53.439 --> 37:56.442
I fart out a coltan-encased
microchip

37:56.609 --> 37:59.028
in cherry pink
and they line up for miles.

38:00.279 --> 38:02.114
Miles!

38:02.281 --> 38:06.118
To carry trackers,
give up their locations,

38:06.285 --> 38:07.662
bank numbers,

38:08.621 --> 38:10.623
fucking facial IDs!

38:11.332 --> 38:14.085
An endless catalogue
of every fuck,

38:14.251 --> 38:19.131
every bite,
every disgusting nose hair.

38:20.967 --> 38:24.679
Every dirty little secret.

38:25.221 --> 38:28.099
Every whisper they thought
no one could hear.

38:30.518 --> 38:32.228
But I digress.

38:32.937 --> 38:35.564
What I'm here to discuss...

38:36.357 --> 38:37.566
is this.

38:40.695 --> 38:45.491
Argus had a lotta fucking eyes.

38:46.242 --> 38:47.326
But...

38:51.330 --> 38:55.793
I have given of my flesh
to my disciples

38:58.087 --> 39:02.425
and they have returned
the favor one-thousand fold.

39:04.093 --> 39:05.177
And now?

39:11.767 --> 39:14.020
Eyes are...

39:20.526 --> 39:22.611
You get?

39:23.779 --> 39:25.281
You ken?

39:27.366 --> 39:29.243
You comprende?

39:36.751 --> 39:39.211
About time.

39:39.378 --> 39:42.923
- Now what are you doing?
- What we came to do.

39:46.385 --> 39:47.928
Candy?

39:48.095 --> 39:50.473
Oh, yes. I want a gold bar
and some nuggets.

39:50.639 --> 39:52.266
Credit or debit?

39:52.433 --> 39:54.477
- Oh, credit.
- Name?

39:54.643 --> 39:57.688
Odin. The Alfather. Never
failed to pay for my candy.

39:57.855 --> 39:59.273
Your name?

39:59.440 --> 40:01.233
Oh, he's just my assistant.

40:01.400 --> 40:02.526
Shadow Moon.

40:07.656 --> 40:11.035
There is no account
under the name Shadow Moon.

40:11.952 --> 40:14.371
That's not the name
on his birth certificate.

40:15.456 --> 40:17.833
There is no account
under the name Shadow Moon.

40:18.000 --> 40:20.461
No debit, no credit.

40:22.546 --> 40:24.757
Oh, so, no debit, no credit.
Not even a fucking car loan?

40:24.924 --> 40:26.926
What are you,
some off-the-grid freak?

40:27.093 --> 40:29.136
I never had any need for it.
Laura did it all.

40:29.303 --> 40:33.140
Do you know how much
Money hates that?

40:33.307 --> 40:35.101
- Access denied.
- No.

40:35.267 --> 40:37.436
This man is not relevant. He's
not looking for an audience.

40:37.603 --> 40:39.146
He's just the hired help.

40:39.313 --> 40:41.232
Access denied.

40:43.234 --> 40:45.236
I am the resurrection
and the life.

40:45.402 --> 40:47.404
Those who believe in me will
live, even though they die.

40:47.571 --> 40:49.490
I am the resurrection
and the life.

40:49.657 --> 40:51.575
Those who believe in me
will live, even though they die.

40:51.742 --> 40:53.661
What does He give you?

40:55.162 --> 40:56.372
Jesus?

40:59.583 --> 41:02.419
It's either I pray
or I run five miles.

41:03.712 --> 41:05.631
And I can't run no more,

41:05.798 --> 41:08.092
jacked up my leg
in Division One, so...

41:10.261 --> 41:12.680
I guess he gives me comfort.

41:12.847 --> 41:15.391
A God should provide
more than comfort.

41:19.103 --> 41:20.437
He does.

41:22.898 --> 41:24.567
Community.

41:25.860 --> 41:27.653
Feeling like there's a point.

41:29.113 --> 41:31.824
I mean, I'm still mad
about my leg,

41:33.200 --> 41:34.910
but if I hadn't messed it up,

41:35.995 --> 41:39.039
I would probably be in college,

41:40.916 --> 41:44.420
and instead I was here with
Gramma while she was sick, so...

41:46.630 --> 41:48.299
maybe it was meant to be.

41:51.135 --> 41:53.596
And maybe I don't gotta be mad
about it, you know?

41:54.555 --> 41:56.724
Gramma prayed for patience:

41:59.268 --> 42:01.145
"Lord, like Job,

42:01.312 --> 42:03.230
let me be patient."

42:04.607 --> 42:06.442
Job was wealthy.

42:06.609 --> 42:08.444
Did her Lord
give her wealth?

42:11.197 --> 42:13.365
This is Cairo!

42:13.532 --> 42:15.743
I don't think money's
got our address.

42:17.620 --> 42:20.789
Last week, I was
reading this blog,

42:21.332 --> 42:23.876
says how in America
the black woman makes

42:24.043 --> 42:26.045
60 cents for every dollar
a white man makes,

42:26.212 --> 42:29.548
and Gramma's all: "Well,
here in Cairo, honey,

42:29.715 --> 42:31.800
a black woman's lucky if she's
got 2 cents to rub together,

42:31.967 --> 42:34.011
and even if she's got
a pocket full of nickels,

42:34.178 --> 42:36.096
that don't mean that
that money's gonna make her

42:36.263 --> 42:38.349
suck a bedsheet up her ass
and fall asleep on a cloud."

42:43.479 --> 42:45.231
And then she laughed real hard.

42:47.942 --> 42:51.320
She was pretty sick,
but she laughed all the time.

42:53.239 --> 42:56.450
She never let anger or jealousy
guide her.

42:59.078 --> 43:01.038
Had her church,
had her community.

43:01.205 --> 43:05.501
She took care of me and Jamarr
when didn't nobody else want us.

43:06.627 --> 43:08.462
She was content.

43:09.713 --> 43:11.382
He was not content.

43:13.926 --> 43:17.429
He was a rebel, a troublemaker.

43:20.432 --> 43:23.143
They say he died for your sins,
but that is not the truth.

43:24.728 --> 43:27.314
He died because he angered
the men in power.

43:29.066 --> 43:31.360
He refused to be cowed...

43:33.028 --> 43:34.154
controlled.

43:36.407 --> 43:38.826
And now look
at the power he wields,

43:40.536 --> 43:43.372
the worship he commands.

43:46.458 --> 43:48.294
He was onto something.

43:52.631 --> 43:54.133
I'm Ruby.

43:55.843 --> 43:57.136
Ruby Goodchild.

44:00.431 --> 44:02.266
It's good
to meet you, Ruby.

44:06.312 --> 44:09.857
Shadow, will you just buy
some fucking candy? Huh?

44:10.733 --> 44:13.736
Do you see me trying?
I mean, look at this.

44:13.902 --> 44:15.821
Huh? They're not gonna sell me
any fucking candy!

44:15.988 --> 44:19.325
Mama-ji just might kill you.
She already wants to kill me.

44:19.867 --> 44:21.702
You know what? Fuck this.

44:22.453 --> 44:23.829
Why me?

44:23.996 --> 44:25.914
- Oh, not that again.
- Yeah, this again.

44:26.081 --> 44:28.083
- Will you just tell me?
- Whimsy.

44:28.250 --> 44:30.210
Why don't you just give me
a fucking answer?

44:30.377 --> 44:31.837
Come on.

44:32.004 --> 44:34.089
- You really want to know?
- Yeah.

44:34.256 --> 44:36.550
You really want to know
why I picked you?

44:36.717 --> 44:38.302
Just tell me.

44:38.469 --> 44:41.388
Well, I picked you
because I needed someone

44:41.555 --> 44:43.807
with nothing to live for,
with nothing to go home for,

44:43.974 --> 44:45.976
with no one to miss him
or love him

44:46.143 --> 44:48.103
or give a shit
if he lives or dies.

44:48.270 --> 44:50.314
That's why I picked you,
because you literally mean

44:50.481 --> 44:52.483
nothing to any living person.

44:52.649 --> 44:54.651
Or any dead one either,
as far as I know.

44:54.818 --> 44:58.697
You have no value, no worth
in this world or the next.

44:58.864 --> 45:00.491
Happy?

45:03.160 --> 45:04.370
Damn.

45:04.536 --> 45:06.163
Good.

45:09.750 --> 45:13.087
See, I've been here
trying to make it all add up.

45:13.253 --> 45:16.382
- Oh.
- Everything since we met.

45:16.548 --> 45:18.384
Oh, really?
How's that going for you?

45:18.550 --> 45:20.469
That little hamster
in the wheel in your brain

45:20.636 --> 45:22.429
make it out yet?

45:24.431 --> 45:25.682
Well, the...

45:27.226 --> 45:29.686
the only thing
that makes any sense,

45:29.853 --> 45:34.024
the only explanation that fits
all the facts, is that...

45:35.943 --> 45:37.486
..I do have value to you.

45:39.822 --> 45:41.824
See, I don't know why.

45:41.990 --> 45:44.660
You don't want me
to know why but...

45:46.829 --> 45:48.580
..you need me.

45:50.040 --> 45:51.166
Don't you?

45:55.504 --> 45:59.716
I am handing you the future
on a motherfucking platter.

46:01.176 --> 46:04.012
I'm gonna need you
to cut that edge pronto,

46:04.179 --> 46:06.432
and put some
fucking garnish on it.

46:07.850 --> 46:09.226
Show me.

46:17.484 --> 46:20.028
I never did see a God

46:20.195 --> 46:25.659
more effectively argue
his own obsolescence.

46:25.826 --> 46:28.537
What the fuck
are you doing here?

46:29.246 --> 46:30.956
Well, go on then.

46:33.083 --> 46:34.626
He's waiting.

46:36.587 --> 46:38.046
Show him.

46:46.138 --> 46:47.264
No?

46:51.518 --> 46:53.020
Then allow me.

47:13.207 --> 47:14.541
Hello, friend.

47:18.420 --> 47:20.005
Hello, friend.

47:25.844 --> 47:27.304
I was literally...

47:28.305 --> 47:30.599
your only friend.

47:34.144 --> 47:36.480
You lonely fuck.

47:43.111 --> 47:47.241
I brought you
into the presence of God.

47:53.121 --> 47:55.374
It looks like he's
forgotten about you.

48:11.848 --> 48:13.058
Mistake.

48:56.143 --> 48:57.185
Fuck!

49:23.003 --> 49:25.964
Wanna buy some candy? Candy?

49:26.131 --> 49:28.425
There isn't a need
to purchase candy.

49:31.511 --> 49:34.139
I retired a God today.

49:34.306 --> 49:36.642
Access granted.

49:42.939 --> 49:45.025
You killed Argus.

49:46.109 --> 49:48.737
And you killed Zorya.

49:50.072 --> 49:52.824
I am sorry about Zorya.

49:54.493 --> 49:56.119
But when you strike
with lightning,

49:56.286 --> 49:58.205
you should
expect consequences.

49:58.372 --> 49:59.915
Mess with my people,

50:00.082 --> 50:02.376
expect disproportionate
consequences.

50:02.542 --> 50:04.586
You got your man back.

50:04.753 --> 50:06.254
It's the principle.

50:06.922 --> 50:08.757
Hello?

50:08.924 --> 50:11.259
