50:16.264 --> 50:18.684
Have you seen what's
happened to the world?

50:20.268 --> 50:23.313
It isn't 5s, 10s, or 20s
anymore. It isn't cash or gold.

50:26.149 --> 50:30.862
It's zeros and ones,
digitized and encrypted,

50:31.697 --> 50:35.117
sent down fiber-optic cables
at the speed of light

50:36.118 --> 50:40.622
to accounts at banks
with no physical location.

50:43.291 --> 50:45.419
Money loves profit.

50:52.467 --> 50:55.178
And war is
always profitable.

50:55.929 --> 50:59.099
It also moves people more
than anything else.

50:59.266 --> 51:01.309
It inflames their passions,

51:01.476 --> 51:03.478
something you would know
nothing about.

51:03.645 --> 51:05.021
And the more passionate
they get,

51:05.188 --> 51:07.065
the more they spend,
spend, spend.

51:07.232 --> 51:08.942
You know that, Money.

51:09.901 --> 51:14.448
You sit at the crossing
of two rivers,

51:15.282 --> 51:19.369
waiting for a steamship
that will never come.

51:20.662 --> 51:23.457
Your kind aren't dying;
they're dead.

51:24.124 --> 51:28.128
Okay, enough -
I'm honored to have

51:28.295 --> 51:31.089
the big dogs in the God game
begging at my table.

51:31.256 --> 51:33.925
But money doesn't make
emotional investments

51:34.092 --> 51:35.802
or invest in emotional entities.

51:35.969 --> 51:38.513
Too much risk
in such ventures.

51:39.264 --> 51:41.475
Not enough opportunity.

51:42.017 --> 51:43.977
You could always
hedge your bets.

51:44.978 --> 51:47.063
There's no deal here for you
today, gentlemen.

51:47.230 --> 51:49.608
Money stays in the bank.

51:49.775 --> 51:51.109
This is agreeable.

51:51.818 --> 51:54.112
What a sad waste of capital.

52:02.370 --> 52:03.997
I'm gonna win this one.

52:04.164 --> 52:06.166
People like me more
